        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:47PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hugo, or 14 miles southeast of Limon, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hugo and Arriba.
</description>
